{
  "text": "Basal vascular tone is a prerequisite for dilator influences. It establishes an underlying arteriolar constriction, a \"regional blood flow reserve\" [CITATION_1] , upon which other control mechanisms produce vasodilation or vasoconstriction.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22635227"
